GETTING STARTED GUIDE FOR polar-ble-sdk
================================================

1. copy polar-ble-sdk.aar to libs folder.
   Minimum android sdk api is 18. 

2. Add these permissions to manifest:

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.BLUETOOTH" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN" />
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION" />
  
3. add following dependency's in build.gradle file:

   implementation files('libs/polar-ble-sdk.aar')
   implementation files('libs/polar-protobuf-release.aar')
   implementation 'com.google.protobuf:protobuf-java:3.1.0'
   implementation 'io.reactivex.rxjava2:rxjava:2.1.5'
   implementation 'io.reactivex.rxjava2:rxandroid:2.0.1'

4. Check example app for code examples. 

5. To see documentation open docs/javadoc/index.html 



